title: Bencze, Quinn qualify for state
text:
Bencze, Quinn qualify for state Oct 23, 2015 Photo by: Dana Royer Gavin Bencze runs at the state qualifying meet in Cedar Rapids. He and teammate Johnathon Quinn qualified for the state meet in Fort Dodge with top-10 finishes. 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
CEDAR RAPIDS — The Winfield-Mt. Union and WACO cross country teams competed at the regional state qualifying meet at Cedar Rapids, Kennedy High School on Thursday afternoon. The W-MU boys had the best day, placing two in the top 10 and finishing seventh overall. WACO didn’t have enough boys to score as a team, and the girls’ teams finished 14th (W-MU) and 15th (WACO). 
Gavin Bencze and Johnathon Quinn were the big performers for W-MU. Bencze came in fourth place, with a time of 16:45, and Quinn finished in eighth place, in 17:07. The two qualified as individuals for the state meet in Ft. Dodge on Saturday, Oct. 31. The 1A boys’ race will start at 2:30 p.m. 
Drake Mehaffy was the third Wolf to cross the line in the boys’ race. He finished 26th, in 18:04. Kohlton Heinzel finished 67th, in 19:22; Ross Vantiger was 103rd, in 21:01; Nick Davis was 107th, in 21:08; and Kane Harris was 134th, in 22:41. 
The W-MU girls were led by Cecelia Hemsworth, who finished 35th, in 22:27. Whitney Vantiger was 79th, in 25:07; Isabella Mertens placed 88th, in 25:52; Kimberlee Warnstaff was 97th, in 26:32; and Fionna Sparrow finished 106th, in 28:15. At press time, WACO individual results are not available. 
BOYS’ TEAM SCORES 
1. Iowa City, Regina 83 
2. Bellevue 1076
